 commonalities between the two are surprising. This is the first book to compare contemporary Indian and European Union approaches to peace and is based on strong case studies and rigorous analysis. Postgraduate students, peace and conflict researchers, policy-makers and practitioners will benefit immensely from insights provided in this book.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPeace-buildingxEuropean Union countriesxEuropexEuropean Union countriesxIndia. 0aPeace-buildingxIndia. 0aPeace-buildingzEuropean Union countries. 0aPeace-buildingzIndia. 4aInternational Relations 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh  aEU.  aIndia.  aconflict resolution.  agovernance.  apeace.1 aBanerjee, Paula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurgess, J. Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurgess, J. Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChadha Behera, Navnita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDasGupta, Sumona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalvanek, Janel B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGhosh, Atig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiessmann, Hans J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobsen, Elida K. U., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLidén, Kristoffer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMac Ginty, Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPogodda, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrakash, Amit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c